error[E0373]: async block may outlive the current function, but it borrows `label`, which is owned by the current function
  --> tests/ui/tokio_spawn_borrows_local.rs:8:18
   |
 8 |     tokio::spawn(async {
   |                  ^^^^^ may outlive borrowed value `label`
 9 |         sleep(Duration::from_millis(1)).await;
10 |         println!("{label}");
   |                    ----- `label` is borrowed here
   |
   = note: async blocks are not executed immediately and must either take a reference or ownership of outside variables they use
help: to force the async block to take ownership of `label` (and any other referenced variables), use the `move` keyword
   |
 8 |     tokio::spawn(async move {
   |                        ++++
